This can't be for play, because you already agreed on hearts as trump
If opener bids 3NT, it says "I have a good hand and I am asking you to start cue-bidding"

If opener starts cue-bidding without bidding 3N, it says "I have an above-minimum, but not great hand"

Example hands - 

you hold @sKJ10xx, @hAxx, @dKQx, @cxx     and open 1@s

Pard bids 2@c and you rebid 2NT
He now bids 3@S showing a better than minimum hand. 
What do you do? You bid 4@s.. You aren't interested in slam, unless partner can do something else
So far, this is just the same as what you already know.|


