That bid by responder says that his hand is probably something like this: 
@sxxx, @hAxx, @dKQJxx, @cAx    and your control bid made his hand look great

Summary: when you have a trump fit and are in a GF auction, if either opener or responder bids 3NT, it says: 
"I have a better than minimum hand for my auction so far, and I want you to cue bid"

If neither partner has extras, you can stop cue-bidding to get out before you get to the 5 level.

There is one other point I want to make about control bids --- 
If you make a control bid (basically, anything you bid in a GF auction after you find a fit) ... 
If the bid is below game, the control bid shows first or second round control. 
If you make a control bid above game, it shows first-round control


